(40, 24, 26, 40, 3, 1, 1, 'in the desert', 'Wilderness Preaching Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of the wilderness as a significant location for divine revelation. Both passages emphasize the importance of discerning true messages from false ones, particularly in the context of where one might find the truth.', 'theme', 0.27899999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 26, 44, 21, 38, 38, 'in the desert', 'Wilderness and False Leaders', 'This connection highlights the theme of deception regarding leadership in the wilderness. Both passages emphasize the idea of individuals leading others into the desert, warning against false claims of authority.', 'theme', 0.27899999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 27, 42, 17, 24, 37, 'so shall also the coming of the Son of man be', 'Connection of the Coming of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the suddenness and visibility of the Son of man''s coming, likening it to lightning. They also share themes of judgment and preparedness, referencing the days of Noah and Lot as examples of unexpected destruction.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 27, 38, 9, 14, 14, 'as the lightning', 'Connection of Lightning Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of lightning, suggesting a powerful and visible divine presence. The comparison of the coming of the Son of man to lightning in Matthew parallels the depiction of the Lord''s arrow going forth as lightning in Zechariah.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 27, 18, 37, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Lightning Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of lightning reaching far distances. Matthew describes the coming of the Son of man with lightning imagery, while Job speaks of God''s lightning extending to the ends of the earth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 27, 23, 30, 30, 30, 'lightning cometh out of the east', 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the dramatic and powerful nature of God''s presence. Matthew describes the coming of the Son of man with a lightning-like appearance, while Isaiah speaks of the Lord''s voice being heard with the imagery of lightning and fire.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 27, 39, 3, 2, 2, 'the coming of the Son of man', 'Connection of Divine Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Lord and the transformative nature of that event. Matthew describes the visibility and suddenness of the coming, while Malachi highlights the purifying aspect of His appearance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 27, 59, 5, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Christ''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the imminent return of the Lord. Matthew describes the coming of the Son of man, while James encourages patience as the coming of the Lord draws near.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 27, 39, 4, 5, 5, 'the coming of the Son of man', 'Connection of Prophetic Coming', 'Both passages emphasize a significant coming event. Matthew speaks of the coming of the Son of man, while Malachi refers to the coming of the great day of the Lord, suggesting a prophetic link between these moments.', 'prophecy', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
