(40, 24, 28, 18, 39, 27, 30, NULL, 'Connection of Eagles and Prey', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of eagles around the slain. Matthew speaks of eagles gathering where the carcass is, while Job describes the eagle seeking prey where the slain are. This connection highlights a thematic parallel regarding eagles and their association with death.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 28, 5, 28, 49, 49, NULL, 'Eagle Imagery in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of eagles, with Matthew referencing eagles gathering where the carcass is, and Deuteronomy describing a nation as swift as the eagle. This connection highlights the use of eagle symbolism to convey themes of judgment and impending danger.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 28, 30, 9, 1, 4, NULL, 'Judgment and Inescapability', 'Both passages emphasize the inescapability of divine judgment. In Matthew, the gathering of eagles suggests a swift and unavoidable consequence, while Amos illustrates that no matter where one tries to hide, judgment will find them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 28, 24, 16, 16, 16, 'there will the eagles be gathered together', 'Gathering of the Unrighteous', 'This connection highlights the theme of gathering for judgment. Both passages depict a gathering of individuals, whether eagles around a carcass or hunters seeking out the lost.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 29, 30, 8, 9, 9, 'the sun be darkened', 'Cosmic Darkness in Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the darkening of celestial bodies as a sign of divine intervention. This connection highlights a theme of cosmic upheaval associated with significant prophetic events.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 29, 29, 3, 15, 15, NULL, 'Cosmic Signs of Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the darkening of the sun and moon, indicating a cosmic upheaval associated with divine judgment. This connection highlights a shared theme of celestial disturbances as signs of significant events.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 29, 23, 13, 10, 10, NULL, 'Celestial Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the darkening of celestial bodies, specifically the sun and moon, as a sign of significant upheaval. This connection highlights a shared theme of cosmic disturbance in times of tribulation.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 29, 23, 24, 23, 23, 'the moon shall not give her light', 'Cosmic Signs of Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize cosmic disturbances as signs of divine intervention. The darkening of the sun and moon in Matthew parallels the confounding of the moon and shame of the sun in Isaiah, suggesting a shared theme of celestial upheaval during God''s reign.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 29, 41, 13, 24, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Cosmic Signs', 'Both passages emphasize the darkening of the sun and moon, as well as the falling stars, immediately after tribulation. This connection highlights a shared apocalyptic imagery in both texts.', 'parallel', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 29, 44, 2, 19, 20, NULL, 'Cosmic Signs Before the Day of the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize cosmic disturbances, such as the sun being darkened and the moon''s altered state, as signs preceding significant divine events. This connection highlights a shared theme of apocalyptic imagery related to the end times.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
